Towns like Great Yarmouth have lost a great deal of their manufacturing industry, while Margate finally lost its famous Hornby model railway factory, along with 400 local jobs, to China in 1995; there’s a Hornby visitor centre there today, at a fiver a pop, but this is hardly the same thing as a working factory or the retention of the skills that the CSJ says are needed here.
